==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blissom
<hw>Blis"som</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[For
<ets>blithesome</ets>: but cf. also Icel. <ets>bl<?/sma</ets> of a goat
at heat.]</ety> <def>To be lustful; to be lascivious.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blissom</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Blissom
<hw>Blis"som</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Lascivious; also, in heat; -- said
of ewes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blissus</ent>⟦br⟧
